<title>Html2Text</title>
<indexterm><primary>Html2Text</primary></indexterm>

<para><anchor xml:id="_md_public_2glpi_2vendor_2html2text_2html2text_2_r_e_a_d_m_e_1autotoc_md6273"/> A PHP library for converting HTML to formatted plain text.</para>

<para><link xlink:href="https://travis-ci.org/mtibben/html2text"></link></para>
<section xml:id="_md_public_2glpi_2vendor_2html2text_2html2text_2_r_e_a_d_m_e_1autotoc_md6274">
<title><title>Installing</title></title>

<para><literallayout><computeroutput>composer&#32;require&#32;html2text/html2text
</computeroutput></literallayout></para>
</section>
<section xml:id="_md_public_2glpi_2vendor_2html2text_2html2text_2_r_e_a_d_m_e_1autotoc_md6275">
<title><title>Basic Usage</title></title>

<para><literallayout><computeroutput>$html&#32;=&#32;new&#32;\Html2Text\Html2Text(&apos;Hello,&#32;&amp;quot;&lt;b&gt;world&lt;/b&gt;&amp;quot;&apos;);

echo&#32;$html-&gt;getText();&#32;&#32;//&#32;Hello,&#32;&quot;WORLD&quot;
</computeroutput></literallayout></para>
</section>
<section xml:id="_md_public_2glpi_2vendor_2html2text_2html2text_2_r_e_a_d_m_e_1autotoc_md6276">
<title><title>History</title></title>

<para>This library started life on the blog of Jon Abernathy <link xlink:href="http://www.chuggnutt.com/html2text">http://www.chuggnutt.com/html2text</link></para>

<para>A number of projects picked up the library and started using it - among those was RoundCube mail. They made a number of updates to it over time to suit their webmail client.</para>

<para>Now it has been extracted as a standalone library. Hopefully it can be of use to others. </para>
</section>
